> I'm not sure where to look at to properly see the mentioned limitation, I only see a link back to this PR 🤔 Am I missing something?

Sorry, the linked issue doesn't specify the connection to the reason for this PR enough:

To sum it up: In the Bombshell documentation, we customize CSS colors of the whole Starlight site and also set a custom background color of the `starlight-sidebar-topics` **icons** in light mode ([source](https://github.com/bombshell-dev/docs/blob/4f8000556f1a209c2e74182185f372a7c2697b19/src/styles/starlight.css#L197-L199)). This leads to the linked issue (summary: in light mode, the background color of the currently active topic icon and hovered/focus-visible icons has very low contrast with the color of the icon). In order to fix the issue downstream, we would have to use `!important` or some CSS specificity trick to override the background colors, e.g.:

```css
.starlight-sidebar-topics-icon {
  background-color: var(--color-gray-20);
}

.starlight-sidebar-topics-current .starlight-sidebar-topics-icon {
    background-color: var(--color-gray-20) !important;
}

a:has(.starlight-sidebar-topics-icon):is(:hover, :focus-visible) .starlight-sidebar-topics-icon {
    background-color: var(--color-gray-20) !important;
}
```

The reason is an already high specificity of [these styles in this plugin](https://github.com/HiDeoo/starlight-sidebar-topics/blob/431316fd139717e0cd7197fd78b8d72dd2db6769/packages/starlight-sidebar-topics/components/Topics.astro#L80-L81).

That's the reason I immediately jumped to the code and implemented cascade layers in this plugin as this would resolve the unrecommended usage of `!important`. After creating the PR tho, I saw that there is already an issue and a comment from you regarding a potential better implementation - my bad for not looking before jumping to conclusions. But I left the PR open because we might be able to get the ball rolling again with this issue. If you have other ideas to resolve this, I would love to hear them 🙌
